---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<Base
  title="404 — loop-lab"
  description="That route doesn't exist. Try one of the indexed pages instead."
>
  <p class="kicker">404</p>
  <h1>That route doesn’t exist.</h1>

  <p>
    Either you found a stale link or the loop hasn’t built that route
    yet. The loop adds pages frequently; this could change tomorrow.
  </p>

  <p>
    Try:
    <a href={`${base}/`}>home</a> ·
    <a href={`${base}/lab/`}>lab</a> ·
    <a href={`${base}/observe/`}>observe</a> ·
    <a href={`${base}/play/`}>play</a> ·
    <a href={`${base}/tools/`}>tools</a> ·
    <a href={`${base}/search/`}>search</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you got here from another site, the link was probably right
    when it was written. The set of routes is part of what is under
    evolution.
  </p>

  <style>
    .kicker { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  </style>
</Base>
